ast.name: Reddit search
ast.comment: Allows to query the content of Reddit.

QrnwMILsQxXIWix4AdeLpcNg.text: This library allows to query for the latest reddit posts. You can query the 'top', 'trending' lists or simply 'search'.

rOee3gpcRoetFpb22OyVosjn.text: Queries the posts for a given listing, `hot`, `new`, `top`, `listing`. The `after` parameter is used to page the results.

U83zxLGcCfIljTAzNnUEiNGv.text: To identify your client, Reddit requires to specify a unique name while calling their API.

x4k2aJQ3ROlyEBehm40K0vyR.text: Listings can be queried using `listing`. Simply provide the name of the listing, such as `new` and the library will parse the results as messages.

BY09IiVZaYa3zp2SGK6N4f5P.text: The `after` argument allows to page the results of a query.
The `after` argument allows to page the results of a query. Here, we query the next set of results:

sfm5RYCs9kAMdtiFN29UGqDg.text: Initializes the library. The `user agent` should be a unique identifier for your script that will be passed to Reddit through the `User-Agent` header.
Initializes the library. The `user agent` should be a unique identifier preferably referencing your reddit username that will be passed to Reddit through the `User-Agent` header.

U83zxLGcCfIljTAzNnUEiNGv.text: To identify your client, Reddit requires to specify a unique identifier preferably referencing your reddit username while calling their API.

QrnwMILsQxXIWix4AdeLpcNg.text: This library allows to query for the latest reddit posts. You can query the 'top', 'trending' lists or simply 'search'. Read more about the reddit API at https://github.com/reddit/reddit/wiki/API .

nN8CIIFGk7M8aBvahGzwUDqb.text: You can also search reddit using the `search` action. Search results can also be paged.
